
Privacy Policy for Mr. Campaign

Last Updated: 3/12/25

Welcome to Mr. Campaign! Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding that data. By using Mr. Campaign, you agree to the terms outlined below.

1. Data We Collect
User Input: The bot processes and stores commands, campaign data, and other user-generated content necessary for its functionality.
Server Information: The bot may store server IDs and settings to provide a customized experience.
No Personal Data: Mr. Campaign does not collect, store, or share personally identifiable information such as real names, email addresses, or IP addresses.
2. How We Use Your Data
To provide and improve the bot’s functionality.
To store campaign-related data for user convenience.
To troubleshoot and enhance performance.
3. Data Storage & Retention
Data is stored securely and used only for bot functionality.
If you wish to remove stored data, contact the bot administrator through the support server.
Data may be deleted periodically to optimize performance.
4. Data Sharing
We do not sell, share, or distribute any user data to third parties.
Data may be shared if required by law or to enforce Discord’s Terms of Service.
5. User Rights & Data Removal
Users can request the deletion of their campaign data by reaching out via the support server.
To opt out of data collection, discontinue using the bot.
6. Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Continued use of the bot after changes implies acceptance.
7. Contact & Support
For questions or data removal requests, join our support server: Mr. Campaign Support.
